to the editor there is something satisfying about waking up the morning after the election to find out that we can not yet say who our next president will be front page nov 8 even in this electronic age in which information is processed and travels extraordinarily fast and in which statistical models allow for remarkably accurate predictions it seems that every vote actually does count and so must be counted technology can certainly help but it only goes so far lisa shapiro northampton mass nov 8 2000

